Backstage at Louder Than Life and Bourbon &amp; Beyond,  The Struts and Marcus King join Fred at his Jack Shack bar set up. The Struts lead singer Luke Spiller defends his recent comments about Queen, while Marcus King may have given a whole new meaning to the bourbon brand Smoke Wagon.&#160;
What they sipped. The Struts: Jim Beam Legacy 15-Year. Marcus King: 1960s Old Crow Traveler Bottle, Smoke Wagon 2 Hot 4 Retail, 2022 Garrison Brothers Guadalupe&#160;
Check out my event Blind Bourbon in Washington, DC, at Nationals Park&#160;

On St. Patrick's Day, Irish singer-songwriter &amp; whiskey aficionado Gareth Dunlop joins the show to taste Redbreast 12 year, Green Spot, Method and Madness and Jameson Black Barrel.&#160;

Gareth just released a new single with touching video starring his son &amp; daughter, "Look Back Smiling" (press release / private album stream). With it, he announced the album Animal &amp; tour with Foy Vance (Ed Sheeran's Gingerbread Man Records) - following his previous tours with Van Morrison, Jeff Beck, Snow Patrol and James Morrison.

Tipped as "one to watch" by BBC, you may have heard Gareth's music in hit shows Nashville, Lucifer, This Is Us, Bones and beyond. His songwriting credits also include Tim McGraw &amp; Faith Hill, T.I. and John Oates.
